<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2006-03-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Reasons for the increase in emerging and re-emerging viral infectious diseases</TITLE><BODY>Abstract In the past two decades, humans have faced many new viral infectious agents in emerging and re-emerging infectious diseases (EIDs). Many factors contribute to the appearance of EIDs. These factors are complex but can be classified into three different categories: virus factors, human factors, and ecological factors. The factors contributing to the cause of such viral infectious diseases will be systematically reviewed in this article.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>